{
  "texts": [
    "Classification algorithms, on the other hand, assist in automated content categorisation, enabling more efficient organisation and retrieval of information (Echedom and Okuonghae, 2021).",
    "On the tactical level, libraries can use AI-driven tools for advanced cataloguing, metadata enrichment and automated indexing, ensuring seamless integration of physical and digital resources (Ahmed et al., 2023; Das and Islam, 2021) and generating more accurate and comprehensive descriptive information, improving discoverability and retrieval (Barsha and Munshi, 2023).",
    "These tools enable libraries to optimise workflows, enhance interoperability with other academic systems and improve the discoverability of resources.",
    "Additionally, AI systems can analyse user feedback and interaction data to refine service offerings, such as personalised recommendations and adaptive learning platforms tailored to the needs of diverse user groups (Deo et al., 2020).",
    "At the operational level, AI can potentially enhance the day-to-day functioning of library services."
  ]
}